{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1135","heading":"Acquisition program baseline breach","label":"1135 Acquisition program baseline breach","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/stI/ch11/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2021—Subsec. (d). added subsec. (d).Pub. L. 116–2832018— renumbered as this section.Pub. L. 115–282section 575 of this titleSubsec. (c). , in introductory provisions, substituted “determination, with a supporting explanation, of whether” for “certification, with a supporting explanation, that”.Pub. L. 115–232"],"amendments":["Amendments2021—Subsec. (d). added subsec. (d).Pub. L. 116–2832018— renumbered as this section.Pub. L. 115–282section 575 of this titleSubsec. (c). , in introductory provisions, substituted “determination, with a supporting explanation, of whether” for “certification, with a supporting explanation, that”.Pub. L. 115–232"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a likely cost overrun greater than 15 percent of the acquisition program baseline for that individual capability or asset or a class of capabilities or assets;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a likely delay of more than 180 days in the delivery schedule for any individual capability or asset or class of capabilities or assets; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an anticipated failure for any individual capability or asset or class of capabilities or assets to satisfy any key performance threshold or parameter under the acquisition program baseline.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Content","label":"b .—Content","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a detailed description of the breach and an explanation of its cause;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the projected impact to performance, cost, and schedule;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an updated acquisition program baseline and the complete history of changes to the original acquisition program baseline;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the updated acquisition schedule and the complete history of changes to the original schedule;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a full life-cycle cost analysis for the capability or asset or class of capabilities or assets;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a remediation plan identifying corrective actions and any resulting issues or risks; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fb%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of how progress in the remediation plan will be measured and monitored.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Substantial Variances in Costs or Schedule","label":"c .—Substantial Variances in Costs or Schedule","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the capability or asset or capability or asset class to be acquired under the project or program is essential to the accomplishment of Coast Guard missions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"there are no alternatives to such capability or asset or capability or asset class that will provide equal or greater capability in both a more cost-effective and timely manner;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the new acquisition schedule and estimates for total acquisition cost are reasonable; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the management structure for the acquisition program is adequate to manage and control performance, cost, and schedule.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Notice to Congress With Respect to Breach of Contract","label":"d .—Notice to Congress With Respect to Breach of Contract","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the terms of the contract that cannot be met; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1135/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1135%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an assessment of whether the applicable contract officer has issued a cease and desist order to the contractor based on the breach of such terms of the contract.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
